Dosage Distribution

What Is The ADA Growth For Students In 3 Weeks After Being Enrolled On an Attendance Focus List?

## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  ada_match$ada_growth
## W = 0.97711, p-value = 8.888e-06
## 
##  Wilcoxon signed rank test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  ada_match$ada_growth
## V = 56070, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true location is not equal to 0

On average, Attendance focus list students improved their attendance for 2.78 days, or by 18.55% in 3 weeks after being enrolled. Typically, Attendance focus list students improved their attendance by 2 days, or by 13.33% in 3 weeks after being enrolled.

ADA Growth by Initial ADA In 3 Weeks

Typical Attendance During Consecutive Weeks of Dosage

This analysis looks at the typical district present days during the consecutive weeks served. Assuming each week is a whole school week, the ADA % is calculated by dividing present days with number of consecutive weeks served times 5. If a student has multiple similar consecutive weeks served, only the ADA on the latest consecutive week is included in the analysis
